MEASURE-THEORETIC DEFINITION
Section::::Measure-theoretic definition.
If P(B) = 0, then according to the simple definition, P(AB) is undefined. However, it is possible to define a conditional probability with respect to a σ-algebra of such events (such as those arising from a continuous random variable).
