CONDITIONING ON A RANDOM VARIABLE
Section::::Conditioning on a random variable.
Conditioning on an event may be generalized to conditioning on a random variable. Let X be a random variable; we assume for the sake of presentation that X is discrete, that is, X takes on only finitely many values x. Let A be an event. The conditional probability of A given X is defined as the random variable, written P(AX)", that takes on the value
